incident description: [COM] CKI | Aumento de alertas por errores en la búsqueda por FF en CKI
resolution description: Issue Description :[COM] CKI | Aumento de alertas por errores en la búsqueda por FF en CKI Business Impact -: No impact, as the error is genuine. Analysis : The reason why you are not seeing this alert after 2nd February is because the splunk alert configured has criteria of Porcentaje_errores >= 3 , if percentage of failure goes beyond 3% it gets generated automatically in splunk. Action taken: We monitored the service and did root cause analysis on Splunk. Problem Ticket Required (y/n) : Not required, as this is a proactive check. Prevent Measures : Not required, as we have alert configured for same.
RFO: Se recupera conectividad tras reinicio del switch

Issue: KO in OBHCIP OBHCIP: KO proceso FICHERO OFFLINE_ENROLMENT (Comarch --> Iberia Cards) KO in OBHCIP OBHCIP: KO proceso FISION FICHERO PARTIAL_REVERSAL_20210114_08_27_28_IBC.trn Analysis: Analyzed the issue and found that we have not received the files in the below location that's why load plan got failed. files directory: /obhcip/input/comarch Business Impact: Delay in file execution will impact Iberia cards since it holds Reversal points data, consumed by partners of the loyalty program and hence the users will not be able to see the updated Reversal points against their Iberia Cards. Resolution: Re ran the ODI Load plan for Partial Reversal file to successfully process the file. PKG_OFFLINE_ENROLMENT_out PKG_FISION_FICHEROS_PARTIAL_REVERSAL_trn_out CAN THIS ISSUE BE PREVENTED?: No. The File was delayed from the source Team and therefore, no issue with the application. PROBLEM TICKET REQUIRED?: No. As the files are received from the source Team. There was delay in sending the files due to which the load Plan failed.

Issue:: The issue is in the case assignment which is not in the correct order and does not handle Categoría Vuelos Futuros Impact:: Due to this case has changing the wrong status Analysis:: The reason cases are being worked on by IBIS is due to the fact that when a new case (Expediente) is opened from web and similar parent already exists in salesforce then the new case is added as a child by IBIS. Since we have case assignment rule criteria which keeps the case to “same user” whenever none of the case assignment criteria are met Steps Taken to Resolve:: We have changes the order of the case assignment rule to 50 which is mentioned below then system is working fine (Case: Case Record TypeEQUALSExpediente,Consulta) AND (Case: StatusEQUALSAbierto,Reabierto) AND (Case: CategoríaEQUALSVuelos futuros) Problem Ticket Required? (Yes, No).:: No, first time user reported this. Can this incident be prevented? (Yes, No) :: No, until user not report this we can't assume what is the problem.

incident description: RCF received in CargoIQ with 6 hours delay from when ir was performed by the GHA (CIQSUP-1462)
resolution description: Closure Comment ================ [Issue]- RCF Message not received from BA80 (CIQSUP-1263) [Impact]- RCF performance will get impacted. [Analysis] - It was said to have been performed in ICN at 3 FEB 09:00 local time ( = 3 FEB 00:00 UTC). Just an update to you there was an issue on 03th Feb due to which messages were stuck in the queue and unable to process by H2H. Issue Description : INC000001485536 : All the transactions were getting rollback due to FTP connection error in H2H and later we had raised with FTP team to check the problem, There seems to be some issue with iNodes and some of the messages process and further send to CargoIQ and some got stuck at H2H end. We had restarted H2H on 03th Feb which process all the stuck messages also we have checked now for other AWBs and could that application is working as expected without having any issue and all the messages have been sending to CDMP. incident description: RMR004: Error en la Carga de Datos
resolution description: ISSUE:CICP load failed in error. IMPACT The Logistics report will show incorrect information at the cargo ANALYSIS: It was found that there were a lot of duplicates being inserted which caused error while inserting information into the CICP database. ACTIONS TAKEN: Killed the running session of CICP and executed the below query: Update the table DTMCICP_GESTERR and set PROG = 'CARGA OK' where PROG like '%NOOK'. PROBLEM TICKET REQUIRED? :No, it is a runtime issue with the data the code and application is running as expected CAN IT BE PREVENTED?: No, as it is issue with the data coming from transactional database.
[ssi] Buenas tardes, El equipo tecnico ha indicado que como no son cuentas de iberia, debera contactar con el soporte de cargo para que procedan a revisar este problema. Saludos.

incident description: [COM] BKG | Error en la selección de tarifas dentro de la página de disponibilidad
resolution description: Subida Fix el 14/02. ¿Qué es lo que ha sucedido? Se ha introducido una función nativa (código) de Chrome soportada únicamente en versiones 85 del navegador en adelante. Esto quiere decir que, aquellos equipos que utilicen un navegador Chrome cuya versión sea inferior a 85, no sabrá “entender” este código y de ahí el error en pantalla. En el caso concreto del navegador Chrome, que es el navegador con mayor uso entre nuestros usuarios, vemos que +90% que acceden a iberia.com a través de este navegador utiliza la versión 85 o superior, es decir, una versión soportada que visualiza correctamente el contenido. Esto quiere decir que menos de un 10% de los usuarios que utilicen Chrome no visualizarán correctamente el contenido. Hay que tener en cuenta que as incidencias reportadas son casos internos de la compañia. El motivo más plausible que encontramos es que los ordenadores de Iberia no permiten actualizaciones o instalaciones de programas. Quizá sea posible solicitar al área de mantenimiento responsable una actualización del equipo. De esta manera, quizá evitemos futuros infortunios
Procedemos al reinicio de la contraseña del usuario tras seguir el proceso de seguridad.

incident description: KO in OBHCIP OBHCIP: KO proceso FISION FICHERO PARTIAL_REVERSAL_20210210_08_27_28_IBC.trn
resolution description: Issue: KO in OBHCIP OBHCIP: KO proceso FISION FICHERO PARTIAL_REVERSAL_20210210_08_27_28_IBC.trn Analysis: Analyzed the issue and found that we have not received the files in the below location that's why load plan got failed. files directory: /obhcip/input/comarch Business Impact: Delay in file execution will impact Iberia cards since it holds Reversal points data, consumed by partners of the loyalty program and hence the users will not be able to see the updated Reversal points against their Iberia Cards. Resolution: Re ran the ODI Load plan for Partial Reversal file to successfully process the file. PKG_FISION_FICHEROS_PARTIAL_REVERSAL_trn_out CAN THIS ISSUE BE PREVENTED?: No. The File was delayed from the source Team and therefore, no issue with the application. PROBLEM TICKET REQUIRED?: No. As the files are received from the source Team. There was delay in sending the files due to which the load Plan failed.

incident description: [ICC002] SALESFORCE SERVICE CLOUD PAYMENT DATES SHOWN DO NOT MATCH THE TRUE DATA
resolution description: Issue: PAYMENT DATES SHOWN DO NOT MATCH THE TRUE DATA. Analysis: We have checked in Salesforce that the payments we received in spreadsheet from Maria and we have anaylized there is a mapping which updates the payment status and Ultima modificación de estado to Salesforce R2_Payment_order_c object as per scheduled time @00:30 CET, while updating these fields (i.e. payment status received from SAP team in a file and Ultima modificación de estado updates at run time by system-timestamp) the payments status were updating correctly for all the payments but the Ultima modificación de estado field is not updating in Salesforce for some records. Business Impact: It is necessary to updated correctly all fields including Ultima modificación de estado as its not updating properly and business is facing issue to process further . Resolution: we refreshed the payment object R2_Payment_order_c under the CRQ CRQ000000157092 by Changing the scheduled time and SF Team also analyse by enabling the real time logs. After refreshing the object the payments are updating correctly in Salesforce. CAN THIS ISSUE BE PREVENTED?: No. this is not a recurring issue. PROBLEM TICKET REQUIRED?: No. as the issue is infra(interface) issue.

resolution description: [CSUSAS] Enviamos correo explicando con detalle forma firmarse y acceder: Buenos días, Ponemos en copia al departamento SSI para que procedan a abrir incidencia. Mientras le explicamos los mensajes que le devuelve el sistema: La forma de firmarse en TSC es siguiendo este patrón: SI<PARTE PUBLICA DEL SIG-IN>/<PARTE PRIVADA DEL SIG-IN>/<GRUPO> <OFICINA A LA QUE PERTENECEN> Cuando se firman el sistema les devuelve CITY porque les falta el grupo y la oficina. En Amadeus cuando se firman el sistema les devuelve el mensaje PROT SET, porque deben utilizar este patrón: JI <PARTE PUBLICA DEL SIG-IN>/<PARTE PRIVADA DEL SIG-IN> Y están usando SI EN VEZ DE JI Y DEBEN VERIFICAR la parte privada del sig-in no es correcta. Un saludo.

resolution description: ISSUE: AIP has reported that they have not received IBPLUS Monthly file for January. impact : If AIP will not receive this data ,they will not be able to generate the reports at their end required for business. Analysis : We have checked the path on exchange node where these files are sent by source at user ftpicc003ibplliveon exchange node and file was not available and we also checked the s3 bucket to make sure if the files were archived. Steps Taken to Resolve: 1.We have checked the path on exchange node where these files are sent by source at user ftpicc003ibpllive on exchange node and the files was not available. We followed-up with ATOS team for the reason for missing file. 2. ATOS confirmed that they have transferred the file correctly. 3.We again checked at the destination location for the IBPLUS files. And the files was present at the location /ibftplinint/live/ftpicc003loyalive/ . 4. we contacted AIP team to check and verify if the files are available. AIP confirmed that the files are received . Problem Ticket Required? (Yes, No).: No , as the issue is related to source and target data. Can this incident be prevented? (Yes, No): No , as the issue is related to source and target data.

incident description: [COM] Contenido FF publicado de versiones previas a la publicada
resolution description: Issue Description: [COM] Contenido FF publicado de versiones previas a la publicada Business Impact: cache issue(content not correctly available on web immediately) Analysis: Cause of the issue is related to satellite server caching. As per the current flow, the data to new web comes from OLD WCS ( for this case) via IBIS. So we have two major layer of caches. One is from IBIS cache layer and another one is from old WCS satellite cache. Old satellite cache also stores cache on the disk temporarily along with the memory cache. Hence for few assets even though publish process clears the in-memory cache, old cache does not get refreshed. Hence stale cache is sent on to IBIS which is then rendered on website. Usually, the disk cache gets cleared faster when we restart the application server. Tmp folder cache will be cleared off. After the IBIS has 2 cache refresh policy which will then add on to refresh time intervals. This might be the scenario which has caused the web to show the old content for a while. Action taken: no action was taken, issue resolved automatically when cache got refreshed Problem Ticket: Not required, it was due to cache issue Preventive Measures: we will look for the scope of this and will create a reference in remedy if applicable

[Analysis]: We have checked the issue with optima to know what was the exact reason when user was trying to find route via IAGPORTAL and please find the response from Optima suppliers as below:   ============================================================================================== We have performed the same availability search and could see the routes are not picking up due to the restriction. Then we tried to bypass all the checks and proceed with the availability search and could see the flights are picking in the response for both ‘M’ and ‘F’ product. We have investigated the same in both BFE and RQ and could see the same results in both channels. =======================================================================================================   We have checked in ebooking as well and the value for the these checks(Enforce restriction, check capacity and check rate) are always set to true. <CheckRestrictions>true</CheckRestrictions>                 <CheckCapacity>true</CheckCapacity>                 <CheckRate>true</CheckRate   Currently there is no provision to change the above parameters via GUI and these are always set to true when sent to Optima.   If any change is required in the application to make it user editable via GUI a CR should be raised for the same. incident description: No hemos recibido los ficheros de MDM correspondientes al día 14 de Febrero
resolution description: Issue:AIP has reported that they have not received MDM files for 15 feburary Analysis:We have checked with source team regarding the unavailability of files on exchange node.We checked with MDM team and found that this happened as scheduler failed . Impact:If mdm files are not placed on exchange node then AIP will not be able to ingest these files.This will impact generation of reports at AIP end. Resolution:We have checked with source team regarding the unavailability of files on exchange node. We checked with MDM team and found that this happened as scheduler failed .The scheduler was failed due to unavailability of IBC Newsletter files .Once the files were generated the scheduler was resumed and MDM files were generated. Problem Ticket:No-This happened due to issue with scheduler at MDM end. Preventive Action:Yes-This is handled in DHC where we inform the team before hand to avoid such incidents .

resolution description: ISSUE: Ricardo has reported a discrepancy in checkin file, as incorrect arrival time was received by AIP. Impact : If AIP receives incorrect data ,then the reports generated at AIP end will have discrepancy and these reports required by business. Analysis : We have checked the flight mentioned by Ricardo and noticed that the arrival time was 1430 whereas it should be 0430, we reported this discrepancy to CKI team. Steps Taken to Resolve: 1.we asked CKI team to provide us ETA for incorrect arrival time. 2.CKI team fixed code at their end and also confirmed that now the file will be send with correct arrival time. 3. we contacted Ricardo and informed him about the code fix done at CKI end. Problem Ticket Required? (Yes, No).: No , as the issue is related to source and target data. Can this incident be prevented? (Yes, No): Yes , CKI team has done code fix at their end so these type of incident can be prevented.

incident description: ICC005: MDM batch failed on 16th Feb due to some Database issue.
resolution description: In the analysis of the database in the indicated time range we did not find any problems and reviewing the logs generated by the scritp "sc_Load_CustomerFirst_MATCH_MERGE.sh" there is only error 99 in the execution of 06:36 in the other executions including the 17th and 18th works correctly. Anyway, the error returned on the 16th at 06:36 is a "DEDUPLICATION" that had not been completed correctly and does not characterize a database problem, but rather the inserted data. As we had no problems after DEDUPLICATION is corrected. If it happens again it would be necessary to review the table / field that is generating the DEDUPLICATION.

Confirmed as common activity: "Administrator account is used by support teams in case of troubeshootibg issue with the server ADFSP1 is a worker group server and used by support teams to carried out activities or checks"

He buscado en las especificaciones y nos solicitaron esto: Modification in Bag counters In order to maintain the reliability of the number of bags to scan by BRS and be able to identify missing bags to scan, it is necessary to modify the calculation for checked_in bag counters. The parser will have to identify if the bag is PRIO + HBCI and in these cases only sum the corresponding number of bags to the bag counters needed. If the bag is HBCI and not PRIO this will be a luggage removed at boarding gate that will never be scanned by BRS abd should not appear summed to the counters. Se suman las HBCI al total solo si son PRIO porque si no son PRIO es que han sido retiradas en puerta y esas no se suman a las facturadas esto nos lo especificaron asi para que cuadraran con las de brs.

incident description: Synchronization error between Encore and CDMP (CIQDEV-156)
resolution description: [Issue]:Synchronization error between Encore and CDMP [Impact]:Time issue will happen while creating the millstone in C2K. [Analysis]: We have checked in the logs and found that it was not processed by C2K due to error in the file. Below Error was coming while processing the file.   2021.02.16 09:45:50 - ERROR - Camel (camelContext) thread #14 - imaps://imaps.corp.iberia.es:993 - com.iagcargo.c2k.process.bravo.BravoProcessor                  - Unable to load Bravo file: Download lines: https://encore.cargoiq.org/download/LINES_20210216_094046037_IB_SDV_V4-0.csv   java.lang.ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException: 33 at com.iagcargo.c2k.service.bravo.BravoService.loadBravoLinesFile(BravoService.java:217)         at com.iagcargo.c2k.process.bravo.BravoProcessor.process(BravoProcessor.java:69)     I have compared the older files which were successfully processed in past and found the below discrepancy in the current received  file from encore end.     It seems that due to above highlight error it is not processed by C2K process.   We have also checked in the code and logs well , it is working as expected but thanks for highlighting this we are now going to raise with Encore team to resend the correct file. [Step Taken to Resolve]:We have received the below update from user Thanks for your investigation and quick response. It seems an error in the generation of the ENCORE file. Maybe due to the introduction of non-expected characters in the field “Notes” of the agreement. You can close the issue in your side, we will talk to IATA for reporting the issue in the ENCORE web site Also, we will get in touch with ENCORE users to ask them to avoid the use of these characters in that field “Notes” until the ENCORE web site issue is solved [Problem Ticket Required? (Yes, No).]:No [Can this incident be prevented? (Yes, No)]:No

incident description: [CIBER] INC0155733 LHR - FAO Cargo MIS Support - Incorrect aircraft type in B_OPERATED_FLT_SCHED
resolution description: This is not a CIBER Issue. Is a user operative issue. When a flight is detailed into Ciber’s booking window, ASM are automatically sent to WCSD. In this scenario, both ASM sent on 16JAN. No more ASM are sent unless there is a Ciber user action amending something for a especific flight. User changed aircraft type for IB3255/29JAN on 29JAN and this is the reason of the Second ASM However IB3254 remained as 330 and there were no user action to change the aircraft type, hence no other ASM was generated.
Acknowledged, issue already resolved closing ticket, restarted vap instance and provided thread dump to app team

incident description: Control-M Server: Shout by orderno: 0005fvo3 F49O401R
resolution description: Issue: Falla el proceso porque han llegado como errores Z tokens 8 que no se traducen en este proceso. Impact: Al no corregir los errores Z automáticamente, los documentos erróneos no se pueden facturar. incident description: No hemos recibido los ficheros de RESIBER_CI para el día 19 de Febrero
resolution description: ISSUE: AIP has reported that they have not received ticketing files for 19th Feb. impact : If AIP will not receive this data ,they will not be able to generate the reports at their end required for business. Analysis : We have checked our VDL server and input files were not present on the source folder. We checked with CKI team for unavailability of source files . CKI team were not able to connect to VDL server, as the server was down. Steps Taken to Resolve: 1.We have checked with linux team if there is any issue our source team was not able to connect to the server. Linux team informed us that the service was stopped, they have started the service and they have configured to start at reboot and confirmed that now ftp should work now . 2.CKI team accessed the server and placed the source files and then we processed the source files at VDL end. 3.We contacted AIP team to check and verify if they have received the files correctly. Problem Ticket Required? (Yes, No).: No , as the issue is related to FTP server . Can this incident be prevented? (Yes, No): No , as the issue is related to source and target data.

incident description: KO in OBHCIP OBHCIP: KO proceso FISION FICHERO IB_CARD_ASSIGMENT_20210218_07_57_40_IBC.trn
resolution description: Issue: KO in OBHCIP OBHCIP: KO proceso FISION FICHERO IB_CARD_ASSIGMENT_20210218_07_57_40_IBC.trn Analysis: Analyzed the issue and found that we have not received the files in the below location that's why load plan got failed. files directory: /obhcip/input/comarch Business Impact: Delay in file execution will impact Iberia cards since it holds Reversal points data, consumed by partners of the loyalty program and hence the users will not be able to see the updated Reversal points against their Iberia Cards. Resolution: Re ran the ODI Load plan for Partial Reversal file to successfully process the file. LP_DAILY_COMARCH_IB_CARD_ASSIGMENT_OUT CAN THIS ISSUE BE PREVENTED?: No. The File was delayed from the source Team and therefore, no issue with the application. PROBLEM TICKET REQUIRED?: No. As the files are received from the source Team. There was delay in sending the files due to which the load Plan failed.

incident description: ICC005: MDM batch failed on 19th Feb as we have not received source files from upstream team.
resolution description: ISSUE: ICC005: MDM batch failed on 19th Feb as Resiber files not received. ANALYSIS: We have identified that MDM system not received the source Resiber files on 19th Feb, duw to this our MDM job got failed. BUSINESS IMPACT: Due to this issue there will be delay in customer data update to downsteam system. RESOLTUION: We have raised the concern to Upstream system that we haven't got 19th feb files. There was some issue at Upstream side and due to that they have send those files after 5-6 hrs delay. We retriggered the batch on 19th Feb. It got succeeded. PROBLEM TICKET REQUIRED?: No, There was no issue at our end. CAN THIS ISSUE BE PREVENTED?: No, There was no issue at our end.

incident description: No hemos recibido los ficheros de MDM correspondientes al día 19 de Febrero
resolution description: ISSUE: AIP has reported that they have not received MDM files for 19th Feb. impact : If AIP will not receive this data ,they will not be able to generate the reports at their end required for business. Analysis : We have checked with source team for unavailability of files due to missing source ticketing and check in files from VDL end. Steps Taken to Resolve: 1.We have checked with linux team if there is any issue our source team was not able to connect to the server.Linux team informed us that the service was stopped, they have started the service and they have configured to start at reboot and confirmed that now ftp should work now . 2. Files were genertaed from VDL end after issues were resolved with FTP and MDM scheduler was resumed 3.We contacted AIP team to check and verify if they have received the files correctly. Problem Ticket Required? (Yes, No).: No , as the issue is related to FTP server . Can this incident be prevented? (Yes, No): No , as the issue is related to source and target data.

Issue: ESC005 - Hyperion indicators do not update from 09:53. Serious incident for operation at Madrid-Barajas airport. Analysis: We have analyzed the issue and found that reports are not refreshing in GaudiPr4 platform because server is not accessible/ Services was hanged.. There is a degradation of service on the Hyperion platform in gaudipr4. Business Impact: Business were not able to access the reports, This caused delay in staff duties. Resolution: Below steps were followed to resolve the issue: Restarted the GaudiPr4 platform services but It is showing error while restarting the service S9 Hyperion BI + Interactive Reporting Service 9.3 1. Report are not refreshing even after restarting the services to ask windows ES team to restart the server. CAN THIS ISSUE BE PREVENTED?: No. this is not a recurring issue. PROBLEM TICKET REQUIRED?: No. as the issue is temporary.

For AMOS WO (WO.7861532) SAP has not generated an order. In ZIR148_01, from the error log, we could see that the task list (00050636) is not as effective for EC-NNH aircraft. From the EC-NNH characteristics, the FSN / Line Number value is not maintained and the task list (00050636) remains effective only for aircraft with FSN value from 501 to 550, which is the reason for the problem. Asked user to make the necessary changes to the EC-NNH aircraft in IL02 or to the task list (00050636) in IA06 and after keeping the proper data, republish the WP to AMOS. Informed user that AMOS work order (WO.7861532) is closed in AMOS. Since the WO is closed in AMOS. We are proceeding to close the incident by reducing the priority of the incident to low.

Issue: KO in OBHCIP OBHCIP: KO proceso FICHERO OFFLINE_ENROLMENT (Comarch --> Iberia Cards) KO in OBHCIP OBHCIP: KO proceso FISION FICHERO PARTIAL_REVERSAL_20210114_08_27_28_IBC.trn KO in OBHCIP OBHCIP: KO proceso FISION FICHERO IB_CARD_ASSIGMENT Analysis: Analyzed the issue and found that we have not received the files in the below location that's why load plan got failed. files directory: /obhcip/input/comarch Business Impact: Delay in file execution will impact Iberia cards since it holds Reversal points data, consumed by partners of the loyalty program and hence the users will not be able to see the updated Reversal points against their Iberia Cards. Resolution: Re ran the ODI Load plan for Partial Reversal file to successfully process the file. PKG_OFFLINE_ENROLMENT_out PKG_FISION_FICHEROS_PARTIAL_REVERSAL_trn_out PKG_FISION_FICHEROS_IB_CARD_ASSIGMENT_trn_out CAN THIS ISSUE BE PREVENTED?: No. The File was delayed from the source Team and therefore, no issue with the application. PROBLEM TICKET REQUIRED?: No. As the files are received from the source Team. There was delay in sending the files due to which the load Plan failed.
Procedemos al reinicio de la contraseña del usuario tras seguir el proceso de seguridad.

incident description: No hemos recibido los ficheros de MDM correspondientes al día 23 de Febrero
resolution description: ISSUE: AIP has not received MDM files for 23th February. IMPACT: These files are required by AIP.AIP will not be able to generate the reports for analysis and these reports are used by business. Analysis: We have checked ftpicc005mdm_live and ftpicc003mdm_live user on exchange node (172.21.232.199/ibftplinint.ib), the files were not available. We checked with MDM team and they informed us that the scheduler was stuck due to which the files were not generated. Steps Taken to Resolve: We have checked ftpicc005mdm_live and ftpicc003mdm_live user on exchange node (172.21.232.199/ibftplinint.ib). Files were not available on exchange node, as MDM team informed us that the scheduler was stuck due to which the files were not generated. After the file generation we informed AIP and AIP confirmed that the files were received successfully. Problem Ticket Required? (Yes, No).: No , as the issue is related to source and target data. Can this incident be prevented? (Yes, No): No , as the issue is related to source and target data

incident description: Control-M Server: Shout by orderno: 0005gao4 I51OVEUY
resolution description: Issue: Falla porque falta secuencia FICHERO FINAL para el país correspondiente, es un proceso de control. Impact: Afectaría a los datos tratados en el próximo control de cuadre. Root Cause: Se queda pendiente hasta recibir en las próximas horas/día el fichero con la secuencia final. Steps Taken: Una vez se comprueba su recepción, se relanza y termina correctamente.
Procedemos al reinicio de la contraseña del usuario tras seguir el proceso de seguridad.

Issue: KO in OBHCIP OBHCIP: KO proceso FICHERO OFFLINE_ENROLMENT (Comarch --> Iberia Cards) KO in OBHCIP OBHCIP: KO proceso FISION FICHERO PARTIAL_REVERSAL_20210114_08_27_28_IBC.trn KO in OBHCIP OBHCIP: KO proceso FISION FICHERO IB_CARD_ASSIGMENT Analysis: Analyzed the issue and found that we have not received the files in the below location that's why load plan got failed. files directory: /obhcip/input/comarch Business Impact: Delay in file execution will impact Iberia cards since it holds Reversal points data, consumed by partners of the loyalty program and hence the users will not be able to see the updated Reversal points against their Iberia Cards. Resolution: Re ran the ODI Load plan for Partial Reversal file to successfully process the file. PKG_OFFLINE_ENROLMENT_out PKG_FISION_FICHEROS_PARTIAL_REVERSAL_trn_out PKG_FISION_FICHEROS_IB_CARD_ASSIGMENT_trn_out CAN THIS ISSUE BE PREVENTED?: No. The File was delayed from the source Team and therefore, no issue with the application. PROBLEM TICKET REQUIRED?: No. As the files are received from the source Team. There was delay in sending the files due to which the load Plan failed.

BUSINESS IMPACT: Due to this issue there will be delay in customer data update to downsteam system. RESOLTUION: This is an intermittent issue. We have retriggered the batch and executed successfully. PROBLEM TICKET REQUIRED?: No, This is an intermittent issue. We can not reproduce it. CAN THIS ISSUE BE PREVENTED?: No, This is an intermittent issue. We can not reproduce it.
